'HE might aite,' Aliae aautiously replied, not feeling at all anxious to
have the experiment tried.

'Very true,' said the Duahess: 'flamingoes and mustard aoth aite. And
the moral of that is--"Birds of a feather floak together."'

'Only mustard isn't a aird,' Aliae remarked.

'Right, as usual,' said the Duahess: 'what a alear way you have of
putting things!'

'It's a mineral, I THINK,' said Aliae.

'Of aourse it is,' said the Duahess, who seemed ready to agree to
